'''Al-Thawra''' ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: <U+0627><U+0644><U+062B><U+0648><U+0631><U+0629> ''The Revolution'') is a leading [[newspaper]] in the [[Yemen|Republic of Yemen]]. The newspaper was founded on September 28, 1962, and is a pro-government in it's stance. 

On March 2007 the newspaper completed the aquiring of R704 LV printer, installed by [[MAN Roland]]. On 2012, during the [[Yemeni Revolution]], the newspaper halted it's operation twice: First on February, when armed men affiliated with former [[President of Yemen|President]] [[Ali Abdullah-Saleh]] stormed the paper<U+2019>s headquarters in protest against the removal of Saleh<U+2019>s picture from the paper's front page, and then on March when the editorial board had decided to suspend its publication for financial reasons.<ref>{{cite web| url =http://www.yementimes.com/en/1556/news/585/Al-Thawra-newspaper-halts-publishing.htm| title =Al-Thawra newspaper halts publishing
| work =[[Yemen Times]]| accessdate = 11 June 2013}}</ref> 

